This paper is about biomedical named entity recognition (NER) using deep learning approaches. The paper specifically focuses on the use of bidirectional language modeling for transfer learning in NER. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and text mining, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper is about biomedical NER, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
